00:17:15,270 --> 00:17:17,000
我会亲自跟她谈  谢谢你  哈桑
I'll speak to her myself. Thank you, Hasan.

339
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,290
谢谢你  大使
Thank you, Ambassador.

340
00:17:30,430 --> 00:17:32,760
莫斯科威胁说要卖武器给伊朗
Moscow is threatening to sell arms to Iran.

341
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,710
他们时常这么威胁
They always make that threat.

342
00:17:34,710 --> 00:17:36,640
耶路撒冷方面认为这个决议案
The feeling in Jerusalem is that this resolution

343
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,790
也许会逼他们铤而走险  不值得冒险
may push them over the edge. It's not worth the risk.

344
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:41,440
你为什么不来找我  还有两小时就要投票了
Why didn't you come to me? The vote's in two hours.

345
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,260
我30分钟前刚接到电话
I got the call 30 minutes ago.

346
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:44,960
俄罗斯不想丢面子
Russia doesn't want to be humiliated

347
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,230
因为我们绕过了他们
because we did this without them.

348
00:17:46,230 --> 00:17:48,220
你知道他们就是虚张声势
You know it's a bluff on their part.

349
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:51,650
总理认为这次投票只是象征性的
The prime minister feels that this vote is just symbolic.

350
00:17:51,930 --> 00:17:53,990
美国不会真的出动军队
That the US won't actually contribute troops.

351
00:17:53,990 --> 00:17:57,210
不  一旦通过  我们绝对会坚持到底
No, we will absolutely follow through once it's passed.

352
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,300
总理有疑虑
The prime minister has his doubts.

353
00:18:00,770 --> 00:18:02,420
抱歉  这不是我能控制的
I'm sorry, it's out of my hands.

354
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,010
克莱尔
Claire?

355
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:09,820
各位大使  我需要你们撤回决议案
Ambassadors, I need you to withdraw the resolution.

356
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:11,160
我们不能达成共识
We lost consensus.

357
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:13,700
我需要推迟投票  直到我们重新达成共识
I need to postpone the vote until we get it back.

358
00:18:16,770 --> 00:18:19,480
特拉弗斯部长是个很好的例子
Secretary Travers is a good example.

359
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:21,340
国土安全部
Homeland Security?

360
00:18:21,650 --> 00:18:24,700
-应该说是前部长  -他下台了吗
- Former secretary, I should say. - He's done?

361
00:18:24,930 --> 00:18:27,260
还没宣布  但史蒂夫打电话给我了
They haven't announced, but Steve called me.

362
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:30,790
说他在联邦应急管理署的事上反对总统
Said he stood up to the president on this FEMA nonsense.

363
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:33,700
国土安全部对联邦应急管理署有管辖权
Homeland Security has jurisdiction over FEMA now.

364
00:18:33,710 --> 00:18:34,500
没错
Right.

365
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:38,520
总统当场要求他提交辞呈
The president demanded his letter of resignation right then and there.

366
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:42,280
-这些都是非正式对话  -明白
- This is all off the record. - Yeah.

367
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:46,690
-保罗真是个大嘴巴  -所以是真的吗
- Paul's got a big mouth. - So it's true?

368
00:18:46,950 --> 00:18:49,270
-这是非正式对话吗  -绝对是
- This is off the record? - Completely.

369
00:18:49,550 --> 00:18:50,980
我用加密电话给你打
Let me call you on my encrypted phone.

370
00:18:50,990 --> 00:18:52,190
我的号码有屏蔽  所以...
My number is blocked, so--

371
00:18:52,190 --> 00:18:54,660
这里是国土安全部  我有你电话
This is Homeland Security. I have your number.

372
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:03,960
有电话呼入  按接听键...
Incoming call. Press the pickup bu--

373
00:19:04,420 --> 00:19:07,740
-部长先生  -是真的  我辞职了
- Mr. Secretary. - It's true. I resigned.

374
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:10,090
那你为什么还在办公室
Why are you still in the office?

375
00:19:10,090 --> 00:19:12,660
点卯撞钟等白宫公布
Punching the clock until the White House wants to go public.

376
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:13,970
如果你反对那项政策
Why wouldn't you go public yourself,

377
00:19:13,970 --> 00:19:15,630
为什么不自己公布消息
if you're so against the policy?

378
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:17,480
我是为总统服务的
I serve at the pleasure of the president.

379
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,100
兰德里已经提供了信息
I have Landry on background.

380
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:21,360
我要写关于辞职的报道
I'm writing about the resignation.

381
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:24,420
我无法阻止你  但你不能引用我的话
And I can't stop you. But there won't be a quote from me.

382
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,930
别让政府逃脱责任
Don't let the administration off the hook.

383
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,510
这是发表反对意见的机会
This an opportunity to speak out.

384
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,130
能做到我这一步
You don't have the career I've had

385
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:35,690
不是靠公开批评上司
by criticizing your bosses publicly,

386
00:19:35,690 --> 00:19:37,530
不管你觉得自己多厉害
no matter how strongly you feel.

387
00:19:38,530 --> 00:19:40,310
和联邦应急管理署的署长阿尼·希尔瓦谈谈
Talk to Arnie Silva, the FEMA Administrator.

388
00:19:40,310 --> 00:19:42,780
他比我更反感这一切
He's more disgusted by all this than I am.

389
00:20:09,330 --> 00:20:13,270
事关人命  他却不管不顾
People's lives are in the balance. And he doesn't care.

390
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:19,230
这是我们接下来12个月的预测
Our projections for the next 12 months.

391
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:21,900
我们正处于拉尼娜时期
We're in a La Niña phase,

392
00:20:21,910 --> 00:20:24,700
也就是说太平洋温度下降
which means falling temperatures in the Pacific.

393
00:20:24,910 --> 00:20:27,940
我们预计这一季至少要发生两次大型山体滑坡
We expect at least two major landfalls this season.

394
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,990
家园被毁  损失数十亿
Homes destroyed, billions in damage,

395
00:20:29,990 --> 00:20:32,160
成千上万人断电
tens of thousands without power.

396
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:35,060
这还仅仅是飓风的危害  要是碰上大地震
And that's just hurricanes. If we get a major earthquake,

397
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:36,810
或者洪水  再或森林火灾
or flood, or forest fire...

398
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:40,320
都在这里面了
It's all in there.

399
00:20:41,710 --> 00:20:43,210
他曾要求你辞职吗
Has he asked you to resign?

400
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:44,360
他威胁过我
He threatened it.

401
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:47,320
但是我说我会配合
But I said I'd cooperate.

402
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:48,950
为什么
Why?

403
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,290
没人比我更有经验
Nobody has more experience.

404
00:20:53,450 --> 00:20:55,740
如果离开  我无法原谅自己
I couldn't forgive myself if I left.

405
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:57,830
但是你刚才不是说  如果赈灾基金耗尽
But you just said, if the Relief Fund is depleted, then--

406
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,240
那人们会受难
People will suffer.

407
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:05,160
但在我的照管下  受难的人能少些
But on my watch, fewer will suffer.

408
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,720
我需要引用你的话  希尔瓦先生
I need a quote, Mr. Silva.

409
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:09,900
我做不到
I can't do that.

410
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:12,650
人命关天  你有责任
People could die, you have a responsibility.

411
00:21:13,030 --> 00:21:15,990
总统创建了一种噤声与恐惧交织的氛围
The president has built a culture of silence and fear.

412
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:17,890
你可以结束它
That can end with you.

413
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:23,320
这个文件夹比任何话语都更有说服力
That folder will speak louder than anything I could say.

414
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:32,130
同一天头版两篇报道都出自鲍德温女士吗
Two front page bylines on the same day for Ms. Baldwin?

415
00:21:32,130 --> 00:21:34,690
真是踢走只斗狗  放进条火龙来
You kicked out a pit bull and you let in a dragon.

416
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:36,950
我没想到《电讯报》能再派一个她这样的
I didn't think the Telegraph would send someone like her.

417
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:38,950
也许你是根本没考虑
Well, maybe you just didn't think.

418
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:41,030
您让我管束他们  先生
You wanted me to implement discipline, sir.

419
00:21:41,030 --> 00:21:42,880
传递讯息  我做了
To send a message. And so I did.

420
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:45,870
他们的回应更强烈  是不是
Well, they've sent back an even stronger message, haven't they?

421
00:21:45,870 --> 00:21:47,590
我对此负责  先生
I take responsibility for that, sir,

422
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:49,570
我会不遗余力让她听话的
and I will do my best to keep her in line.

423
00:21:49,570 --> 00:21:51,170
不遗余力
Your best?

424
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,120
有他们总编辑保着  谁也碰不了她
It's their top bureau chief. She's untouchable.

425
00:21:54,170 --> 00:21:57,050
我不想假装我能百分之百控制她
I don't want to pretend that I can control her 100 percent.

426
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:59,260
-特拉弗斯  -他否认曾与她谈话
- Travers? - Denied speaking with her,

427
00:21:59,260 --> 00:22:00,570
但是肯定是他
but it must be him.

428
00:22:00,740 --> 00:22:02,540
我想内阁中再没别人会了
I don't think anybody else in the cabinet would.

429
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:03,980
我们确认他辞职一事
Let's confirm his resignation.

430
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:05,900
现在还保密没意义了
No point in keeping it a secret now.

431
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,730
告诉史蒂夫他可以把办公室清空了
Tell Steve he can vacate his office.

432
00:22:07,730 --> 00:22:09,020
那希尔瓦呢
And what about Silva?

433
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:11,990
关于防灾预测的细节相当专业
The details on the disaster projections are very inside baseball.

434
00:22:11,990 --> 00:22:14,600
我们不能炒了他  如果飓风来了
We can't fire him! If there's a hurricane,

435
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,630
他是唯一能防止灾难变成浩劫的人
he's the only guy that can keep a disaster from becoming a catastrophe.

436
00:22:17,630 --> 00:22:20,460
-邓巴说什么  -还没有公开表示
- And what's Dunbar saying? - Nothing yet, publicly.

437
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:22,150
她可能想让好戏演到终场
She's probably letting this play out.

438
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:24,350
让我自掘坟墓
Letting me dig my own grave.

439
00:22:26,490 --> 00:22:29,360
我们必须推销《美国就业法案》
We have to sell America Works.

440
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,190
等人们有工作  就不需要别的吹捧了
It should sell itself once we get people employed.

441
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,700
是要这效果  但我们不能止步于此
Well, that's the idea, but we don't stop there.

442
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:36,250
-广告和公告牌  -用谁的钱
- Commercials and billboards? - On whose money?

443
00:22:37,270 --> 00:22:39,120
即使这样  广告也不够
And even so, we need more than ad-buys.

444
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:43,360
我们需要...挖掘它背后的深意
We need... We need the philosophy behind it.

445
00:22:43,370 --> 00:22:46,600
我们需要实质性的东西  我们需要...
We need something of substance. We need something...

446
00:22:57,980 --> 00:23:02,140
我们需要能启发想象力的东西
We need something that will capture the imagination.

447
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:05,530
-你们玩《纪念碑谷》吗  -那是什么
- Either of you play Monument Valley? - What's that?

448
00:23:05,530 --> 00:23:07,380
-是一款游戏  -我不玩游戏  先生
- It's a video game. - I don't play them, sir.

449
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:09,630
我在易趣上把Xbox卖了  玩着太上瘾
I sold my Xbox on eBay. It was too addictive.

450
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:11,380
不  不是主机游戏
No, it's not a console game.

451
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:12,690
你们读读这个
You both read this

452
00:23:12,690 --> 00:23:15,140
然后告诉我你不想玩这个
and then tell me that you wouldn't want to play this.

453
00:23:19,110 --> 00:23:20,710
我敢说全国只有九个顾问
I'd say there's nine consultants in the country

454
00:23:20,710 --> 00:23:22,200
真正懂得外交政策
who truly know foreign policy.

455
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,080
我是第一
Me, I'm number one.

456
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:26,160
失去意识的我是第二
Me in a coma is number two.

457
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:28,320
但是还剩下七个逊于我的呢
But that still leaves seven who are cheaper.

458
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:29,680
我重视良言
I value good counsel,

459
00:23:29,780 --> 00:23:32,310
我也有足够脑子知道自己的欠缺
and I'm smart enough to know what I don't know.

460
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:34,230
截至目前你对我们的评价如何
What would be your assessment of us so far?

461
00:23:34,230 --> 00:23:36,250
迈克尔·科里根的事你处理得一团糟
You're making a big stink out of this Michael Corrigan thing,

462
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:37,800
但这还只是表面上的
but that's just surface.

463
00:23:37,930 --> 00:23:40,270
你得明白科里根为何被捕
You have to understand why Corrigan got arrested.

464
00:23:40,270 --> 00:23:42,480
佩特罗夫想迎合传统观念人群
Petrov's appealing to his traditional base.

465
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:45,880
不  这与约旦河谷有关
No. This is about the Jordan Valley.

466
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:47,310
我不太明白
I don't follow.

467
00:23:48,180 --> 00:23:49,210
复仇
Retaliation.

468
00:23:49,450 --> 00:23:51,220
这得回溯到几个月前的峰会上
It goes back to the summit a couple of months ago.

469
00:23:51,220 --> 00:23:56,050
这里是约旦河谷
Look, this... is the Jordan Valley.

470
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,120
等一下  我放到大屏幕上去
All right, hold on, I'll make it easier.

471
00:24:06,310 --> 00:24:08,410
这是河谷  在这里
That's the Valley. Right there.

472
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,590
1967年以来一直归以色列
Occupied by Israel since 1967,

473
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:13,640
一直是与巴勒斯坦达成和平协定的拦路虎
it's been a major roadblock in any peace accord with the Palestinians.

474
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:16,480
安德伍德派维和部队过去  以色列人走了
Underwood sends peacekeeping troops, the Israelis leave,

475
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:19,340
-巴勒斯坦人开心了  -没那么简单
- the Palestinians are happy. - It's not that simple.

476
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:22,060
所有人都为这个小地方牵肠挂肚
Everyone gets hung up on this little patch of land ten miles by 40,

477
00:24:22,060 --> 00:24:23,380
但你得往远了看
but you have to look outwards,

478
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:25,820
越过约旦  叙利亚还有伊拉克
past Jordan and Syria, past Iraq.

479
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:29,710
这里  高加索山脉
Here... to the Caucasus.

480
00:24:30,030 --> 00:24:31,540
这里是俄罗斯的地盘
That's Russia's sphere of influence.

481
00:24:31,540 --> 00:24:34,120
他们不觉得维和部队是中东问题
They don't see the peacekeeping force as a Middle East issue.

482
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:36,280
而是觉得这是美国军队的战略调度
They see it as strategic deployment of US troops

483
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,220
离他们南部边界不到一千里
less than a thousand miles from their southern border.

484
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:41,240
你是说  科里根只是一枚棋子  一个筹码
So you're saying Corrigan's a pawn, a play for leverage?

485
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:42,880
更像是打响的第一枪
More of a first salvo.

486
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:45,860
莫斯科要表明对反抗决议案的决心
Moscow wants to show it's serious about fighting this resolution.

487
00:24:46,030 --> 00:24:47,420
要我猜的话
Now, if I had to guess,

488
00:24:48,050 --> 00:24:50,270
安德伍德在峰会时本想拉拢俄罗斯
Underwood tried to bring Russia into the mix during the summit.

489
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:52,440
成为合作伙伴
Get involved early on as partners.

490
00:24:52,630 --> 00:24:54,210
但佩特罗夫不肯合作
And when Petrov didn't play ball,

491
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:57,830
安德伍德就转守为攻  是场豪赌
Underwood went on the offensive, which is a huge gamble.

492
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:00,620
-怎么说  -没人想让联合国军队过去
- Tell me how. - Nobody wants UN troops there.

493
00:25:00,620 --> 00:25:02,300
以色列人不想  巴勒斯坦人不想
Not the Israelis, not the Palestinians,

494
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:03,310
阿拉伯人也不想
not the Arabs.

495
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:05,740
他们合作都是因为美国的施压
They're playing along because the US is pressuring them.

496
00:25:06,230 --> 00:25:08,280
但只要有一点差错
But just one little thing needs to go wrong,

497
00:25:08,420 --> 00:25:11,080
所有人都拿着火柴等着点你的炸药包
and you've got a tinderbox where everyone's holding matches.

498
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:14,550
那他为什么要采取这样的行动
So why is he following this course of action at all?

499
00:25:15,030 --> 00:25:16,190
因为他很聪明
Because he's smart.

500
00:25:16,710 --> 00:25:18,820
-可你刚说  -他是聪明过头
- You just said-- - He's being too smart.

501
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:22,610
要是这招行得通  他能拿诺贝尔奖
If it pays off, hey, he wins a Nobel Prize. But...

502
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:28,250
但行不通的话  他毫无反击之力
if it backfires, he leaves himself wide open.

503
