as someone who shies away from a challenge.

857
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:44,070
我得按我自己的方式写
I'd need to be able to write it the way I want to write it.

858
00:46:44,090 --> 00:46:47,250
没问题  多待一会儿  看看风景
Absolutely. Look, take your time. Enjoy the view.

859
00:46:47,250 --> 00:46:48,860
看完了密查姆会送你出去
Meechum will show you out when you're done.

860
00:46:48,860 --> 00:46:52,840
我保证  你答应了绝不会后悔
And I promise, if you say yes, you won't regret it.

861
00:46:55,170 --> 00:46:58,160
有水平的作家都不会拒绝好故事
No writer worth his salt can resist a good story,

862
00:46:58,460 --> 00:47:02,180
就像政客总忍不住乱许诺言一样
just as no politician can resist making promises he can't keep.

863
00:47:10,650 --> 00:47:13,480
维克多  受邀前往是我们的荣幸
Viktor, we'd be honored to accept the invitation.

864
00:47:14,390 --> 00:47:17,310
是啊  要谈的事太多了
Yes, I agree, there's much to discuss.

865
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:20,050
我会叫我的办公室联系克里姆林宫
I'll have my office reach out to the Kremlin.

866
00:47:20,050 --> 00:47:22,200
安排一个都方便的日期
We'll find dates that work for both of us.

867
00:47:23,970 --> 00:47:24,920
谢谢
Thank you.

868
00:47:25,710 --> 00:47:28,120
你该睡了吧  那边都好晚了
Well, you should get some sleep. It's late over there.

869
00:47:29,720 --> 00:47:30,630
晚安
Good night.

870
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:33,700
表决暂缓
Hold off on the vote?

871
00:47:34,130 --> 00:47:37,050
等谈了再说  不过留着这一手
Until we sit down. But we keep it in our back pocket.

872
00:47:37,630 --> 00:47:38,820
迈克尔·科里根呢
Michael Corrigan?

873
00:47:39,890 --> 00:47:41,840
我们到访的时候释放他
They're going to release him when we visit.

874
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:44,080
你造就了奇迹
You made a miracle happen.

875
00:47:44,760 --> 00:47:45,700
是我们
We did.

876
00:47:54,590 --> 00:47:57,730
每一位独一无二的公民都影响着未来
...each unique citizen contributes to our future.

877
00:47:57,730 --> 00:47:58,740
能大点声吗
Can you turn that up?

878
00:47:58,740 --> 00:48:02,080
我们的先辈宣布独立时
Our forefathers, when they declared independence,

879
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:05,050
就理解个体的力量
understood the power of the individual,

880
00:48:05,050 --> 00:48:07,830
自主的价值
the value of self-determination.

881
00:48:07,830 --> 00:48:10,240
他们把我们从暴政中解放出来
They freed us from tyranny.

882
00:48:10,240 --> 00:48:11,660
-他们证明了...  -他就是暴君
- They proved... - He is a tyrant.

883
00:48:11,660 --> 00:48:13,530
不好说  那里那么多人
I don't know, there's a lot of people out there.

884
00:48:13,530 --> 00:48:14,850
他也许做对了
He might be onto something.

885
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:17,250
下行政命令调派维和部队  他疯了吧
Executive Order for UN troops? He's out of control.

886
00:48:17,250 --> 00:48:19,810
至少他有所行动  沃克什么都没干
At least he's doing something. Walker didn't do shit.

887
00:48:19,810 --> 00:48:22,560
我们弹劾了个哑炮  换了个原子弹
I think we replaced a dud with an atom bomb.

888
00:48:22,900 --> 00:48:25,660
他们的自由是抗争得来的
They had to fight to secure their freedom.

889
00:48:25,670 --> 00:48:28,970
如今我们也要通过抗争保住自由
And now we have to fight to maintain it.

890
00:48:28,970 --> 00:48:31,070
工作的自由
The freedom to work.

891
00:48:31,070 --> 00:48:33,950
体面活着的自由
The freedom to live with dignity.

892
00:48:33,950 --> 00:48:36,550
希望的自由
The freedom to hope.

893
00:48:36,650 --> 00:48:41,200
谢谢你们  天佑美国
Thank you, and God bless the United States of America.

